git init  	 // initialize local git repository (hidden file)
git add <file>   // add files to index, you can add many times before commiting 
git status       // check status of working tree
git commit	 // commit changes in index
git commit -m 'put your message here'
git rm --cached <file> 	// to remove a file from index area
git add . 	// to add every file, same as:
git add * 


### each time that you change a file you need to add it to the index area and then commit it

##### for remote repository
git push         // push to remote repository
git pull         // pull the latest changes from the remote repository
git clone 	 // copy a remote repository into current directory	 
git merge  <name of the branch to merge to a destination branch>	//while we are in the destination branch	
git branch	// to see names of the all the branches 
git branch <name of the branch>
git checkout  <name of the branch to get in>	// to get out of the current branch and
						// get in another one   
git remote 	// lists the address of remote repository linked to our repository
git remote add origin  <https:...  .git>   



#### How to install GIT

Linux (Debian):		 $sudo apt-get install git
Linux (Fedora): 	 $sudo yum install git
Mac, Windows:		 http://git-scm.com/download/mac  (win)
(for windows when you install git, choose the last option "Use Git and optional unix tools from the windows cammand prompt"
for the rest just keep the default, After installing uncheck the view Release Notes and check the Launch Git Bash)


git --version	// for getting the version



#### To add your name and email address to your git
git config  --global user.name 'Razyeh Behbahani'

git config  --global user.email 'Behbahani.razy@gmail.com'


######### To make an ignore file, not to commit or record their changes in your gir repository
touch .gitignore	// make a hidden file, you can use vi or nano 
#### we need to add the name of the file or /folder that we want to be ignored to .gitignore file
#### If we want to exclude all *.mif files we can just add *.mif to the .gitignore file  
 
